<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="293">
diagnosis A large member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group most similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181813" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obscurithorax Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obscurithorax Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurithorax">obscurithorax</taxonomicName>
of Argentina (and exotic in the southern U. S.), and somewhat less so to the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181822" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole puttemansi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole puttemansi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puttemansi">puttemansi</taxonomicName>
, differing as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Major: robust; hypostoma 2-toothed; entire head heavily sculptured, with genae, venter, and broad median strip (including frontal lobes) longitudinally carinulate and most of the remainder, from genae to occiput, rugoreticulate; most of pronotal and propodeal dorsa transversely carinulate; anterior strip of first gastral tergite shagreened; promesonotal convexity in dorsal-oblique view strongly lobose and directed posteriorly; petiolar peduncle very thick, petiolar node low; postpetiole laterally angulate, scape broadened at insertion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Minor: occiput narrow, with nuchal collar; head and pronotum shiny; propodeal spines reduced to denticles. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 2.00, HL 1.96, SL 1.06, EL 0.24, PW 0.94. Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.80, SL 1.00, EL 0.16, PW 0.46.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Color Major: gaster and postpetiole dark reddish brown, rest of body medium reddish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Minor: gaster dark reddish brown, rest of body light to medium reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Range Known only from the type locality and from Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil (J. C Trager).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="293">Biology The type colony was collected in cerrado, or tropical savanna. A seed cache was found in the nest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
